    'subj' => 'sensor rule of thumb for ship designers',
    'from' => 'Bruce Alan Macintosh',
    'body' => 'The rule of thumb is that you can see a normal target - a 100-ton ship
with no masking (sig=0) at a range equal to your sensitivity (Impossible)
